quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  68,43,"Their sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i><i class=""s"">(subdued) </i>in reverence, humiliation overwhelms them, for they had been called to prostrate themselves when they were sound."
  68,44,"So leave<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Me to those who reject this discourse; We will draw them forth gradually<i class=""s"">(to punishment) </i>from where they do not know."
  68,45,"And I will give them respite. Indeed, My plot is firm."
  68,46,"Or do you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>ask them for a reward, so they are burdened with debt?"
  68,47,"Or do they have<i class=""s"">(knowledge of) </i>the hidden realm and they are writing it down?"
  68,48,"So wait patiently for the Decree of your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord, and do not be like the Fellow of the Whale, who cried out in despair."
  68,49,"Were it not for his Lord’s favor that reached him, he would have been thrown into the wilderness, fully despised."
  68,50,"But his Lord chose him and made him one of the righteous."
  68,51,"Those who have denied almost stab you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>with their sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>when they hear the Reminder, and say, “He is indeed a madman!”"
  68,52,"But it is nothing other than a Reminder to<i class=""s"">(all creatures of) </i>all realms."
  69,1,"The Reality."
  69,2,"What is the Reality?"
  69,3,"And what can make you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>realize what the Reality is?"
  69,4,"Thamûd and ʻĀd disbelieved in  the Shocking Event."
  69,5,"So as for Thamûd, they were annihilated by the Overwhelming."
  69,6,"And as for ʻĀd, they were annihilated by a furious, roaring wind"
  69,7,"which He unleashed upon them for seven nights and eight days in succession, so you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>could see the people tossed around as though they were stumps of hollow palm trees."
  69,8,"So can you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>see any remnant of them?"
